commit_message:
DVR: Create separate routing table for routers in fip namespace

The fip namespace is shared between tenants on a given compute node.
So far the fip namespace was only used for forwarding floatingip
traffic, but with the fast-path exit, this namespace will also be
used for forwarding the traffic directly to the external network
without floating IPs if the address scopes match.

In order to provide flexibility in adding the different next hop
routes for the external network, each router will now have a dedicated
table that hosts the routing rules.

The traffic is matched based on the incoming interface and forwarded
to the route lookup table.

The table index is generated from the fpr-interface ip so it should
be unique on a given node.

Change-Id: I5c46ab99d0b9482a2a2012d2e5abb7f293ae4f36

commit_message:
Collapse devmode definitions on release file

Collapsing devmode definitions on config file and removing release file
created side effect when scripts and defaults expected to find a release
definitions.
This patch moves all devmode definitions on the release file instread,
removing the need to specify devmode.yml as extra configuration file.

Change-Id: Id651f90b0c28f9aa402eb6f78713bc22633ad88c

subject: Convert to unicode explicitly to avoid UnicodeDecodeError
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-09-14 08:56:06.000000000', 'files': ['sahara_dashboard/content/data_processing/data_plugins/workflows/update.py'], 'message': "Convert to unicode explicitly to avoid UnicodeDecodeError

In a zh-cn environment in horizon, when click the button of updating
plugin, chinese characters can lead to error.
Because the type of 'prefix_trans' is non unicode but 'name' is unicode.
Python will decode 'prefix_trans' firstly. If 'prefix_trans' contains
chinese characters then will lead to errors saying out of range 128.
So we convert 'prefix_trans' to unicode explicitly and python will not
decode because both 'prefix_trans' and 'name' is unicode. In fact,
'prefix_trans', 'prefix' and 'name' will be unicode at last.

Change-Id: I75f3334f7e6bac9dc2819ac2632636ece95efc31
Closes-Bug:#1622864
"}]
commit_message:
Convert to unicode explicitly to avoid UnicodeDecodeError

In a zh-cn environment in horizon, when click the button of updating
plugin, chinese characters can lead to error.
Because the type of 'prefix_trans' is non unicode but 'name' is unicode.
Python will decode 'prefix_trans' firstly. If 'prefix_trans' contains
chinese characters then will lead to errors saying out of range 128.
So we convert 'prefix_trans' to unicode explicitly and python will not
decode because both 'prefix_trans' and 'name' is unicode. In fact,
'prefix_trans', 'prefix' and 'name' will be unicode at last.

Change-Id: I75f3334f7e6bac9dc2819ac2632636ece95efc31
Closes-Bug:#1622864

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-13 03:38:54.000000000', 'files': ['designate/backend/impl_infoblox/connector.py'], 'message': 'Infoblox backend:Fixed sslverify value from option

Infoblox connector always passes sslverify value with value True if we
set sslverify False in pools.yaml file . Since connector module
assumes it is empty value and  it goes to getattr function and set the
attributes for sslverify as True after reading from config file which
is default value.

Eventually connector sends the wrong configuration of sslverify to
python requests module and hence the exception occurred.

Change-Id: I903254ec4aa8f6e0230c78ed7b22aab0e0326190
Closes-Bug: #1618688
Closes-Bug: #1620462
'}]
commit_message:
Infoblox backend:Fixed sslverify value from option

Infoblox connector always passes sslverify value with value True if we
set sslverify False in pools.yaml file . Since connector module
assumes it is empty value and  it goes to getattr function and set the
attributes for sslverify as True after reading from config file which
is default value.

Eventually connector sends the wrong configuration of sslverify to
python requests module and hence the exception occurred.

Change-Id: I903254ec4aa8f6e0230c78ed7b22aab0e0326190
Closes-Bug: #1618688
Closes-Bug: #1620462

commit_message:
Set permissions on the openstackgit directory

The change removes the constraint that would skip setting the directory
permissions in certain cases. Now permissions will be recursively set
and the task will follow symlinks should it encounter any at the provided
path.

This should solve permission related issues on playbook reruns and the
permissions will always be correctly set by the role.

Change-Id: I3d974d578f3e2323415e36c40efa48036b517468
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Add check for swift_hash_path_ variables

We should never change the swift_hash_path_prefix/suffix variables on a
running cluster. This PR implements a check that will fail if the
variable is different to what is already on disk.

To ensure this is still possible this PR implements a
"swift_force_change_hashes" variable which can be set to "True" in order
to force change the swift_hash_path variables regardless of whether they
are different or not.

Change-Id: Idaedc125aede22c347668afd9e98ed1823eb142c

Specify which type of config we are using for the deployment

running. It's avoid to use some tricks for counting the number
of compute or controller nodes (for example).

commit_message:
fix port address allocation for auto-addr subnet

AutomaticAddressRequest is created manually in
add_auto_addr_on_network_ports.
But expected workkflow is to use address request factory, that can be
overriden by ipam driver to deliver custom AddressRequest classes.
Added code to follow expected workflow.
Now factory method called for SLAAC allocations, so third party ipam
driver can deliver custom AddressRequest for these allocations.

Change-Id: I95d6097a6bc30107e2819c484e9718f6a5ee619e
Closes-Bug: 1570465

revisions:

On a running galera cluster, we don't want to unintentionally allow a
galera_cluster_name from changing. This will cause a cluster to fail to
start (if the nodes are restarted sequentially) as the cluter name value
has changed.

To ensure we can still change this value, a new
"galera_force_change_cluster_name" variable is added, which can be set

Change-Id: I8bae038bd207a15d5731b9c91b78df851a4c1986

commit_message:
Prevent galera_cluster_name from changing.

On a running galera cluster, we don't want to unintentionally allow a
galera_cluster_name from changing. This will cause a cluster to fail to
start (if the nodes are restarted sequentially) as the cluter name value
has changed.

To ensure we can still change this value, a new
"galera_force_change_cluster_name" variable is added, which can be set
to "True" in order to change the cluster name.

Change-Id: I8bae038bd207a15d5731b9c91b78df851a4c1986

commit_message:
Tag the alembic migration revisions for Newton

This allows the database to be upgraded with the command:
  neutron-db-manage upgrade newton

Migration f399fa0f5f25 is the newton milestone for the expand
branch. It was tagged earlier (although it shouldn't have been).

Migration 61cc795e43e8 was erroneously tagged, so remove the
tag from there.

Also clean up a deprecated use of model_base because the
deprecation warning was cluttering up the output of
neutron-db-manage.

Depends-On: I5b9c02814bdc1945422184a84c49f9e67dcf24a9

Partial-Bug: #1623108

Change-Id: If1820978c1eb6a8c2dbff20b349c0d4108a49258

commit_message:
Zero tolerance for errors on nodes as default behavior

Without this change we do not mark deployment as error
if task on node failed.

Also use early initialize of logger for support library
Deployment

Change-Id: Ibcac4569756b34c3c1ac33f68ae203246d94d2a4
Closes-Bug: #1620858

commit_message:
Use memory mode for sqlite in db test

Config option sqlite_db is deprecated in
0a1bae9859079fb21a03716be947c5f1da6db0a2, and deprecate argumentsqlite_db in method set_defaults in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/350945/, should use config option
connection instead. For watcher, we test database with sqlite in memory
mode [1] as below:

cfg.CONF.set_override("connection", "sqlite://",
                      group="database", enforce_type=True)

and don't use config option sqlite_db, so remove unused code.

[1]http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_1_0/core/engines.html#sqlite

Change-Id: I9b1f995e1b7004bcfe6c5a854c2f83b24e5bfb56

revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2016-09-12 12:42:32.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py'], 'message': 'libvirt: fix live-migration with serial console check

If the graphical consoles VNC and SPICE are disabled and the serial console
is enabled, the live-migration of an instance will result in an ERROR state.
This is due to the move in commit 917afd2831b. The "can migrate" verification
from the late "_live_migration_operation" step to the earlier
"check_can_live_migrate_source" step . The "listen_addr" variable will then
always be None, and the check for the serial console in
"_verify_serial_console_is_disabled" will then be a false negative.

This change adds the "serial_listen_addr" to the migration_data object
in the "check_can_live_migrate_destination" step, so that the step
"check_can_live_migrate_source" can access it and make a decision based
on that.

Closes-Bug: 1595962
Change-Id: I94fad08a31bc1d90c95c13f34fe4e9b74e0920ac
'}]
commit_message:
libvirt: fix live-migration with serial console check

If the graphical consoles VNC and SPICE are disabled and the serial console
is enabled, the live-migration of an instance will result in an ERROR state.
This is due to the move in commit 917afd2831b. The "can migrate" verification
from the late "_live_migration_operation" step to the earlier
"check_can_live_migrate_source" step . The "listen_addr" variable will then
always be None, and the check for the serial console in
"_verify_serial_console_is_disabled" will then be a false negative.

This change adds the "serial_listen_addr" to the migration_data object
in the "check_can_live_migrate_destination" step, so that the step
"check_can_live_migrate_source" can access it and make a decision based
on that.

Closes-Bug: 1595962
Change-Id: I94fad08a31bc1d90c95c13f34fe4e9b74e0920ac

commit_message:
Message correction on cli for Delete VNF call

When the user issues a vnf-delete command, it gives output message
as 'Deleted vnf: <vnf id>'. With the new behavior of
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/291032/ , output message should
be like 'Request to delete VNF <vnf id> has been accepted'

Closes-bug: #1573194

commit_message:
Introduce proposal jobs for ironic-python-agent CoreOS version

Currently, the CoreOS version is pinned in the ironic-python-agent
repository. This requires manual commits in the repository for any
update to happen. This approach was prefered instead of building from
latest at all times to prevent a CoreOS release from breaking our gates.

This commit introduces a proposal job to bump the CoreOS version. It
does so by leveraging the existing proposal scripts to submit changes
for new CoreOS versions as they become available. This approach allows
us to gate new CoreOS releases so they do not impact us, and allows us
to benefit from the latest updates.

Closes-bug: 1600228
Change-Id: Icf94aed2811912e46d7de1aa002903299122b3f7
Depends-on: I78cb2efff2293b1591b30b7e39df9fc2af98d0b2

commit_message:
Add non-voting python 3 tempest jobs

The change I3a1dfde76009cbac1d419e0ff3f1d20c4a2e99c3 tests
devstack with the python 3 switch flipped where we see
gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-full passing. The job currently
installs python clients/commands that are exercised in
devstack and services that have the python3.4
classifiers(currently Keystone and Neutron) to run using
python 3.  However, the changes mentioned in the below
depends on patch would have to be merged before see a
successful tempest run.

For a start, add tempest-dsvm-neutron-full-py3-nv jobs to
the integrated gate and tempest-dsvm-neutron-src-{name}-py3-nv
jobs to lib-forward-testing.

Depends-On: I4ca6366d4a4d1b007d12e7cd3975506e101d42c0

Change-Id: I9a086f5452a42667dd6b1575a57381402aca3726

commit_message:
Add alias for OS_ENDPOINT_TYPE

Some service clients do not respect the old OS_ENDPOINT_TYPE
parameter, instead only supporting the newer fashion of
OS_INTERFACE which is viewed as less confusing. This adds support
for that option.

Failure to include this causes SSL certificate errors when the
service clients attempt to use the public endpoint with a self-
signed certificate on defaulted installs, particularly AIOs.

This error can be demonstrated by trying to use the Gnocchi or new
Aodh clients from a utility container, though only the Gnocchi
client is currently installed in the integrated build.

Change-Id: I60af4f0cf56964eaec8980264ec1ebadc550c0b8
(cherry picked from commit e14f1f39200d734d01361fafa667c8dc19096ce3)

commit_message:
Change image type to RAW in osic-cloud8

Since we run ceph backend, having RAW image is much better for
performance as instead of copying data Ceph handles CoW shapshots

Change-Id: I4c838e8ed850a57c19697ab472840b4ba69c94f5

commit_message:
Configure admin NIC prior the first system boot

Having admin NIC confugured in the middle of system booting
is very fragile and error-prone approach.
It's better to configure it ahead of first booting time.

Also, there's no need for freaky networking restarting inside of
cloud-init boothooks anymore.

Change-Id: I4c278341e8b40eb8d9b100bed1d9a650f27b5c5b
Related-Bug: #1583815

commit_message:
Update openstackclient commands

This updates the spec to reflect the changes that were done
during implementation of the osc commands. In particular:
- it was decided not to provide two commands (differing in
  spelling) for the same thing, so 'passthru' instead of
  'passthrough'
- not to implement osc commands that are equivalent to
  'ironic driver-raid-logical-disk-properties' and
   'ironic driver-properties' because we aren't sure (yet)
   what the "right" command might be

Change-Id: I1f146e73ea342f07d65dcc985a5e94f2c8a98fd0
Closes-Bug: #1526479

commit_message:
Degrade failing identity-v3 job to experimental

The job gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-identity-v3-only-full-nv seems to be
failing constantly for more than a month now, see the related bug.

Trying to fix the issue has been unsuccessful so far, in particular
I haven't been able to reproduce the failure locally. So in order to
conserve resources, make the job experimental until it can be fixed.

Change-Id: Ibed550fe615fc3a1ad4fb94e5e88f2ccafab0c90
Related-Bug: 1620999

commit_message:
Upgrade a single package or a bunch of packages

It takes package names and versions from hiera hash to upgrade
and override "ensure" parameter in package resource.
If any package from the current puppet catalog is upgraded,
all the services in the same catalog should be restarted.

If there are no upgraded packages, then no services to be restarted.

Change-Id: Ic79cffb2b92cc0380261f5980263d84b7434a7f4
Closes-Bug: #1623038
Related-Bug: #1616553

commit_message:
Fix race between setup-bootdev and network

Redesign systemd units in the following way:
1) Move setup-bootdev unit from /etc to /usr and create symlink to /etc.
That prevents systemd to create unit from init.d script.
2) Add dependencies to setup-bootdev to run it before network.service.
3) Add fix-configs-on-startup unit and force to run it after
network-online target.
Now we have following well defined order: setup-bootdev -> network ->
-> fix-configs-on-startup ->(mcollective,ntp and other services)

Change-Id: Iefa83096924259efbc4eb30359b9a19b3466e121
Closes-Bug: #1621468

commit_message:
Override PXE kernel cmdline via Glance property

Override PXE kernel cmdline via Glance property to allow images to boot
with a custom kernel command line. This is important because some images
requires different kernel command lines to identify which root filesystem
it needs to boot, for example, when booting from an LVM volume the root
filesystem should come from device mapper like "root=/dev/mapper/os-root".

This patch also allows Ironic to use this feature in the standalone mode,
if Glance is not available operators could set the custom kernel command
line to the node's instance_info['kernel_cmdline'] field directly and
that will be used when PXE booting the image.

Implements: blueprint override-pxe-options-via-glance-property
Co-Authored-By: Blake Caldwell <blakec@ornl.gov>
Change-Id: Icb070addf59c0ed62f2b2aac8fc597fdf8cf2a5a

commit_message:
Format the valid fields for list commands

When using list commands with 'fields' argument, the error info of
valid fields should contain both resource.fields and resource.labels.

The commands are:
chassis-list
chassis-node-list
node-list
node-port-list
port-list
chassis-show
node-show
port-show

Change-Id: Ie6c9a5cbf25c973f6ec3220017cd76df1da84eba

commit_message:
Enable 'text' format sort for enterprise databases

For some enterprise relational databases, such as db2, the
'text' column in database can not be used in 'ORDER BY' sql
commands. These columns need to be transformed and casted
to the sortable variables when facing these specific
databases, while for the databases that support 'text'
such as mysql, this cast will not be done. That means the
'CAST' is only desired for those backends which require it,
and it will not break the default mysql path.

The 'last_error' and 'maintainence_reason' in table nodes
should be transformed and casted to the sortable text format
when using as the sort key for these enterprise relational
databases.

I did the testing both in mysql and db2 env, works fine.

Change-Id: I384b0a7755e6ef7fa874a44b5f551877732a9512
Closes-Bug: #1446508

commit_message:
Add keyring support

This patchset adds keyring support to ironic client. Currently,
the user has to expose the password either through the command
line or by configuring an environment setting so that the
password is not prompted on every command. Adding the keyring
support will help in secure storage of the password and avoid
prompting the password every time.

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-13 09:43:18.000000000', 'files': ['ironic/common/service.py', 'ironic/cmd/conductor.py', 'releasenotes/notes/honor-perodic-tasks-intervals-314d7ff13409d09a.yaml'], 'message': "Ironic conductor to honor the interval values for periodic tasks

interval values configuration for the periodic tasks. Since the interval
values are passed to a decorator the configuration options should be

commit_message:
Ironic conductor to honor the interval values for periodic tasks

This patch fixes a problem which was preventing Ironic from honoring the
interval values configuration for the periodic tasks. Since the interval
values are passed to a decorator the configuration options should be
evaluated prior to importing the module which contains the periodic tasks.

In our case this is not happening because there's a chain of imports going
from ironic.cmd.conductor -> ironic.common.service -> ironic.api.app
-> ... -> ironic.conductor.manager which is making the @periodic
decorators to be evaluated before the configuration options.

This patch breaks that chain of imports by importing ironic.api.app inside
the scope it's being instead of the beginning of the file. We also add an
assert statement as a safeguard to guarantee that ironic.conductor.manager
is not loaded earlier in the startup of the process and prevent similar
errors to sneak in again.

Closes-Bug: #1562258
Change-Id: I16c6e5a9ed0879b9b5f3949ffc4b0d58c67a97fa

commit_message:
Add new project Trio2o

Trio2o is to provide APIs gateway for multiple OpenStack clouds
to act as a single OpenStack cloud.

Trio2o is derived from the Tricircle. Move Nova API-GW/Ciner API-GW
away from the Tricircle into new dedicated Trio2o project, and
only networking automation part will be remained in the Tricircle,
i.e, the Tricircle will noly include local Neutron plugin, central
Neutron plugin, Admin API and XJob. And Trio2o will
includes the Nova API-GW/Cinder API-GW/Tricircle admin API/XJob.

After the moving, the Tricircle project will focus on the networking
automation across Neutron.

The repository will import from the upstream Tricircle repository,
code cleaning will be done after the repo established.

(gerritbot is not configured for it reaches 120 channels limit)

Change-Id: Icf2d909457d295eb204604933dad47cec2a0c309
Signed-off-by: joehuang <joehuang@huawei.com>

commit_message:
Add iscsi_opc and agent_opc to manage the OpenPOWER servers

This patch adds iscsi_opc and agent_opc driver changes.
The modification includes the following:

- Refactor the functions in pxe_utils.py to support pxe and
petitboot boot drivers.
- Use class method to refactor the module function in pxe.py
- Add petitboot boot driver
- Add iscsi_opc and agent_opc drivers to manage the OpenPOWER
servers

Related-bug: #1526265
Change-Id: I3642fcc587bbbf712dee072ec7df98856a37d50e

commit_message:
Add check 'role' existence in release

Now Nailgun doesn't check 'role' existance in release
that leads to 'Internal Server Error 500' while trying
to get/update/delete non-existing roles. This patch adds
check role procedure and returns 404 not found responce
instead Internal Server Error.

Change-Id: I9a9e0fc59a86b414dce1fc3b036b90d00db94325
Closes-Bug: 1617229

commit_message:
share-size not set to 1 with 'manage_error' state

Currently, when we set share-state to 'manage-error', share-size
is set to 1 at all places except this one. Which results in error
logged during delete-share, w.r.t quota.

This fix sets share-size to 1 when share state is
set to 'manage_error'.

Change-Id: I96343ffd4f273b01c0376713717cdc89ea9a873a
Closes-Bug: #1587636

subject: Cassandra fix lost keyspace(s) after cluster grow
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-18 15:22:29.000000000', 'files': ['trove/common/strategies/cluster/experimental/cassandra/taskmanager.py'], 'message': "Cassandra fix lost keyspace(s) after cluster grow

A seed node does not bootstrap, so a new node can't be configured
as one immediately. It may be promoted only after bootstrapped.

Also fix comprehension conditions. Nodes must be compared
on 'id'.
They cannot be compared as objects because each
contains a reference to guest instance.

Change-Id: Iaf8115548e54457a672048ed0e9d296ae893013e
Closes-Bug: 1614577
"}]
commit_message:
Cassandra fix lost keyspace(s) after cluster grow

A seed node does not bootstrap, so a new node can't be configured
as one immediately. It may be promoted only after bootstrapped.

Also fix comprehension conditions. Nodes must be compared
on 'id'.
They cannot be compared as objects because each
contains a reference to guest instance.

Change-Id: Iaf8115548e54457a672048ed0e9d296ae893013e
Closes-Bug: 1614577

commit_message:
Implement FluentFormatter

This change implements FluentFormatter, a formatter for fluentd.
It enables oslo_log to output logs to fluentd directly.
FluentFormatter expects it will be used by fluent.handler.FluentHandler.

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint fluent-formatter
Change-Id: I67be5079f9370e93e5e3d4c715d2b8011154a2ce

commit_message:
Use correct version when creating backup dir

Currently, when performing a liberty->mitaka upgrade, we back up
/etc/openstack_deploy to /etc/openstack_deploy.MITAKA, but in liberty
branch we used /etc/openstack_deploy.KILO.  This commit updates scripts
and docs to reference the correct directory, which is
/etc/openstack_deploy.LIBERTY.

Change-Id: I4d193981400f2fb45eb827b2ee1e23c919f2c8fd

commit_message:
Reduce minimum data disk size for the AIO to 55GB

Some OpenStack-CI providers do not meet the current minimum
of 60GB. Bluebox in particular is providing instances with
a root disk size of around 58GB.

Current job results show that we are able to reduce the
minimum to just over 50GB.

This patch sets a new minimum of 55GB for the AIO bootstrap
but intentionally leaves the documented minimum in the AIO
quickstart at 60GB as that is a more practical minimum for
developer testing.

Change-Id: Ibca491a9fac3e7e6d650d024658dc11a0890648f

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-13 21:29:14.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/openstack-ansible.rc'], 'message': 'Fix log path option

The log path option is attempting to log to a directory that may not
exist. To fix this the "openstack-ansible.rc" file will now check if
the log path directory exists and if it is missing an attempt will be
made to create it. Should there be any issue in creating the log
path directory the variable will be unset allowing Ansible to continue
without emitting an error message.

Change-Id: Ic7827f35df3a7005b24db79e5b374f5e4ed1282b
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Fix log path option

The log path option is attempting to log to a directory that may not
exist. To fix this the "openstack-ansible.rc" file will now check if
the log path directory exists and if it is missing an attempt will be
made to create it. Should there be any issue in creating the log
path directory the variable will be unset allowing Ansible to continue
without emitting an error message.

Change-Id: Ic7827f35df3a7005b24db79e5b374f5e4ed1282b
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
teach latest-deliverable-versions to diff against the dashboard

Add an option to latest-deliverable-versions so that when it is given a
CSV dump of the release dashboard it compares the version information it
finds in the deliverable files to what is in the dashboard and reports
on anything that is different.

Change-Id: I55e16755d6e8d39cb7cb7e4266a5163d59f5baa0
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Delete some unnecessary initial value = None

If the function, the parameter initial value is set to None, and
then use the xx = xx or [] , that is unnecessary, I made two
experiments:

def a1(msg=None, properties=None):
    msg = msg or []
    print(msg)
a1()

def a2(msg=[],properties=None):
    msg=msg
    print(msg)
a2()

C:\Python34\python.exe C:/Users/Administrator/PycharmProjects/untitled10/a.py
[]
[]

These two kinds of method is the same,doing so can reduce unnecessary
None references

Closes-Bug: #1623368
Change-Id: Ifed794e04d47985ca1a3022a1604bc816626b144

commit_message:
Fix Rollback port's device_owner

From this patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/341427/
Sometimes, port doesn't revert device_owner to previous value
in concurrent requests case.

This patch fixes this problem and adds unit test.

Change-Id: I864a559f0316e164caa065abd75c44fae971b571
Closes-Bug: #1621750

subject: track the branch we're testing separately from the series we're given
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-13 18:48:53.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_releases/cmds/list_changes.py'], 'message': 'track the branch we're testing separately from the series we're given

Keep track of which branch we're examining when looking at the value of
HEAD so we can print a more sensible message when the SHA for a new tag
matches. This is especially useful for independent projects, so we get
messages like "Request releases from HEAD on stable/foo" instead of
"Request releases from HEAD on stable/_independent".

Change-Id: I4990d4bf2e9cc996e217cac71f56f6ef64cf974b
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>
'}]
commit_message:
track the branch we're testing separately from the series we're given

Keep track of which branch we're examining when looking at the value of
HEAD so we can print a more sensible message when the SHA for a new tag
matches. This is especially useful for independent projects, so we get
messages like "Request releases from HEAD on stable/foo" instead of
"Request releases from HEAD on stable/_independent".

Change-Id: I4990d4bf2e9cc996e217cac71f56f6ef64cf974b
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Zero tolerance for errors on nodes as default behavior

Without this change we do not mark deployment as error
if task on node failed.

Also use early initialize of logger for support library
Deployment

Change-Id: Ibcac4569756b34c3c1ac33f68ae203246d94d2a4
Closes-Bug: #1620858

commit_message:
Explicitly name FK "cisco_router_mappings_ibfk_2"

If foreign key in cisco_router_mappings is created without
specification of name the latter will be auto-generated.
This leads to issues while trying to delete it later under
name "cisco_router_mappings_ibfk_2" in plug-in upgrade code
for any DB engines but InnoDB.

Change-Id: I486e7eac2e5b4cfea2452148c85d28ca6bb75756
Closes-Bug: #1623041

commit_message:
[placement] don't write existing equivalent allocations

If an allocation PUT is made that exactly matches existing
allocations for the current consumer_id, don't write, just respond
with the usual 204.

This allows a resource tracker which is in a state of being over
allocated to still write allocations and know that the placement
service has the data.

Change-Id: I777964845e9aa563bc0947af7b7c31df497202e9
Closes-Bug: #1619723

commit_message:
Use requests-mock for testing

Instead of directly mocking out the HTTPClient use requests-mock to stub
the information that is going over the wire instead of what is being
passed to HTTPClient. This ensures that the HTTPClient is always tested
as well.

Change-Id: I988fb432ced6d4946ab5301ac58fa0d7148bbb79

commit_message:
Add filters to 'fuel2 task list' command

Now Nailgun supports filtering transactions by statuses,
cluster_id and transaction_types
(commit 8257a0dbcb680e4eb9c19afe027b3a0fbdb0e7be).
This patch adds filtering support for 'fuel2 task list' command.

usage: fuel2 task list [-h] [-f {csv,html,json,table,value,yaml}]
                       [-c COLUMN] [--max-width <integer>] [--noindent]
                       [--quote {all,minimal,none,nonnumeric}]
                       [-s SORT_COLUMN [SORT_COLUMN ...]] [-e ENV]
                       [-t {pending,error,ready,running}
                           [{pending,error,ready,running} ...]]
                       [-n NAMES [NAMES ...]]

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: 1613674

Change-Id: I8e33944a422a7847e055318b9d73e872244117c7

commit_message:
Move libnetwork specific options to its own group

This patch separates the libnetwork specific options from other common
options with other components such as Raven and put them into
"libnetwork" group. The libnetwor remote driver will have its own
configuration in libnetwork.conf, which is typicall located in
/etc/kuryr/libnetwork.conf.

Change-Id: I8ee0977d7864ef24e9502d0d374d8b084b3f2959
Signed-off-by: Taku Fukushima <f.tac.mac@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Antoni Segura Puimedon <toni@midokura.com>
Closes-Bug: #1572823

commit_message:
Add option to toggle list extensions

By default a list item in a JSON or YAML format will extend if a its already
defined in the target template and a config_override using a list is being set
for the existing "key".

This change allows that functionality to be toggled on or off. The boolean
option to enable list extension is ``list_extend``.

To maintain the API this feature will remain True by default.

Co-Authored-By: Travis Truman <travis_truman@cable.comcast.com>
Change-Id: I97e06aef2cc778f048f3d6863fe61d10eddb8602
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Ensure that gnocchi uses keystone authentication

The upstream default implementation of gnocchi is not
to use keystone authentication, but a preferred deployment
configuration in enterprise environments is to ensure that
keystone authentication is configured.

This patch ensures that keystone auth is enabled if keystone
is implemented in the environment.

Closes-Bug: 1622251
Depends-On: Ic41cf161af1d59e5b0f4b71c0d698cd7348c962c
Change-Id: Iaac6174f5588856a594ca646ed869d637c04d95a

commit_message:
Add package upgrade functionality in fuel-library as Fuel Basic LCM approach

    File /etc/hiera/override/common.yaml should contain hashes which describe package names and versions
    Example of common.yaml:
    static_versions:
      openssh-client: '1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.8'
      libcurl3 : '7.35.0-1ubuntu2.8'
      mc : latest
    group_versions:
      ^apache2.*$ : '2.4.7-1ubuntu4.13'
      ^grub.*$ : latest

    As an option,  "^.*$ : latest"  can be added in group_versions hash to apply a MU

Change-Id: Id33665df73a5eb9fdb6773e941ea855d0017b90d

commit_message:
Implement extra_properties handler

Add an interface to receive notification updates of images' extra
properties from glance.

Cinder store will use this information to choose an image volume's
type based on its "cinder_img_volume_type" property. This property
specifies the volume type for a new volume created from the image.
Cinder can create it quickly by cloning the image volume when both
the image and new volumes have the same type. Therefore, cinder
store can optimize the process by storing the image volume with
the specified type.

Change-Id: Ica3bf8ee761848101fd6c7aa85c3bbd0bf4124e5
Depends-On: Idb8f1e595472fd955d14e634063af50259a8dbb0

commit_message:
Notify extra properties changes to glance_store

On creating image, pass the extra properties to glance_store
for hinting to optimize for each store.
When the extra properties are updated, call glance_store's
_set_extra_properties() to notify the changes.
Currently only cinder store will use it to enable cinder to
create new volumes by cloning the image volume.

Change-Id: I95a4d413a80c2f9f46b14c1580a02ebefdd8aa87
Depends-On: Idb8f1e595472fd955d14e634063af50259a8dbb0

This adds a hook to add the populate_existing() call to
all SQLAlchemy queries issued by Neutron.

This is necessary because we don't expire objects on
commit so a DB object will prevent new lookup queries
from getting new data about that object until it is
garbage collected or explicitly expired.

Populate_existing() informs SQLAlchemy to update all
objects in the session with the data retrieved from
a query. More details can be found at the following link
and in the docstring inline.
http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/orm/query.html#

"}]
commit_message:
Add populate_existing() to all queries

This adds a hook to add the populate_existing() call to
all SQLAlchemy queries issued by Neutron.

This is necessary because we don't expire objects on
commit so a DB object will prevent new lookup queries
from getting new data about that object until it is
garbage collected or explicitly expired.

Populate_existing() informs SQLAlchemy to update all
objects in the session with the data retrieved from
a query. More details can be found at the following link
and in the docstring inline.
http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/orm/query.html#
    sqlalchemy.orm.query.Query.populate_existing

Change-Id: I2f8c618e1cd3b32a86004fb081741d2a389693fd

commit_message:
Enable install redis server with package manger

1. It is unnecessary and slow to install redis from source code
2. If people run stack.sh and it fails after redis has been installed,
they have to unstack all components before they run stack.sh again,
otherwise stack.sh will fail because it can not be installed again
from the source code

Change-Id: I2aa83aed83510e93fbf2af438e6f099897cad953

commit_message:
clarify the "unexpected API error" log message

A lot of bug reports in Launchpad attach only (if at all) the n-api log
file when they get an unexpected API error and I assume it's the log
entry which makes them believe this is all we need to debug an issue.
As we need quite often the n-cpu or n-sch logs, this change tries to
clarify this log entry.

Change-Id: I44952182f59bc94d4cd1a446823796609912d4e4

commit_message:
Support publishers that set value to None

Some publishers (e.g. ZMQ driver) set the 'value' field in an event to
None. Other publishers (e.g. redis) keep the value field.

The change here allows support to both types of drivers.

Change-Id: Ib6e6d6efefed1edf9a13c0ec1bb4d5e91b32c7aa

commit_message:
Remove Ceph from the ha job

Now that we've re-enabled the nonha job we're testing ceph there,
so we can remove it from the ha job and reduce the number of nodes
needed by one.  This should also speed up the ha job.  Also, at the
moment we aren't testing the non-ceph path at all in our check jobs
which is not good either.

Also switches the nonha job to use storage-environment.yaml so we
keep coverage of that file.  It turns out there's no practical
difference between that and puppet-ceph-devel now because the
composable work removed the deployment of osds on controllers.

Change-Id: I67a4a6f9348e181204d5ee5afe377b8e65066dc1

commit_message:
VMAX driver - Won't delete pre-existing initiator groups.

If an initiator group has not been created by the VMAX
driver (i.e. pre-created on the array with a different
name to OS-<shorthostname>-<Protocol>-IG), it should not
be deleted by the driver if it has no more masking views
associated with it. This patch adds in a check to ensure
only initiator groups created by the VMAX driver are
deleted.

Change-Id: I5217ed4822590f00ae8c80d636e56905f320f6e8
Closes-Bug: #1618784

commit_message:
clarify requirements diff portion of list-changes output

Show the changes for each requirements file separately, so it is easier
to tell what are test-related changes and what are runtime changes. The
separate files were always named, but the formatting of the output
before made it easy to not notice which changes were part of which file.

Change-Id: I6209410219f3fc97c7d1ae54042da7cf05dc8891
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Replace agent elements with package python-heat-agent-puppet

This change replaces the overcloud image build elements
heat-config-puppet, heat-config-script with the package based
equivalent python-heat-agent-puppet.

python-heat-agent-puppet depends on python-heat-agent which does the
setup of os-collect-config, os-refresh-config, os-apply-config for
heat bootstrap, and also installs the script hook.

This vastly improves the in-place upgrade story since it will work
like any other package upgrade.

Originally in I84c4fb2b222e7d196061b4684acdd89391fde7f4, this patch
is for the new tripleo-build-images in tripleo-common.

Change-Id: I3a399caeab5e35f409f162205291f2dfaa2566d3

iptables rules.

commit_message:
Make cfn functions inherit from HOT

HOT is our canonical native format, so define the cfn intrinsic functions
in terms of the HOT functions instead of the other way around. Ensure each
function has a consistently-formatted docstring appropriate to its template
type.

Change-Id: I743446bdef3fd7472537db75bf9e0fbfb164e36a

commit_message:
Utilize retry_if_session_inactive in dvr_mac_db

Adds the retry decorator to the DVR mac DB module and
leverages its ability to retry on DBDuplicate entries
to simplify the code.

We also add a transaction guard to make the previously
implicit assumption that _create_dvr_mac_address would
be called outside of a transaction explicit.

Partial-Bug: #1612798
Change-Id: I0c919a3f08e0be1aea4e28dc8f6d92b51de129e0

commit_message:
Support for evaluated resp body in service client tests

Some service client may manipulate response dict for example
identity v3 credential clients load the nested dict 'blob'
into response object before returing it.

So in those cases, base class helper should excpect evaluated body
tests class instead of consuming the service client specific logic.

This commit makes suppport of same and update credential_clients
tests for that.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I586400ded9d18c0cbb19be0424fbe5f7b1ce798d

commit_message:
Load complete json response in List credentials

Identity credential client list API return response object
with nested dict 'blob' as string which should be loaded into
dict before returning from service client.

This commit makes complete response body including nested dict
to be loaded before returning.

This was missed in I0ae04d76738fe6f639d90af8c142bdbc6a1fa83f
when this client was moved to lib but it is not yet released
so should be safe to fix this.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I31fa2e114dd8872ecf7393c8ba61a0359baed5e8

commit_message:
Fix race condition updating routes

Generic driver updates routes on host according to the tap
interfaces created for use by share servers. That code
should be within a lock to prevent a thread failing to delete
a route previously listed and already deleted by another thread.

This change moves an existing lock to the function that
performs route changes while also covering the function
that had the lock before.

Closes-bug: #1617461

Change-Id: I798e5d9b0bc9ebefc8661d0ade720c60303cf484

commit_message:
Replace  assertDictEqual() with assertEqual()

In unittesttools, assertDictEqual() and assertEqual()
are implemented by using '!=' operator. But assertEqual()
can handle dict, list, set and so on.
So we should use assertEqual() to make the test simpler.

TrivialFix.

Change-Id: I72918e74b7352d27a1cbe6c6c134f1746db7604b

commit_message:
Replace assertDictEqual() with assertEqual()

In unittesttools, assertDictEqual() and assertEqual()
are implemented by using '!=' operator. But assertEqual()
can handle dict, list, set and so on.
So we should use assertEqual() to make the test simpler.

TrivialFix.

Change-Id: Ic0dc690c5dfa83567fb428d554b8b591dbf4414a

commit_message:
Add header blocks to all Dockerfiles

Change needed to add header blocks to all Dockerfiles, similar to the
base.

Use case is to easily run something before packages are installed, e.g.
to COPY a local rpm in that can be added to the package list.

Change-Id: I1bbfdf0b762da0a392aa8bf47781315b45377bee
Closes-Bug: 1618969

subject: Using sys.exit(main()) instead of main()
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-08 09:00:12.000000000', 'files': ['heatclient/shell.py'], 'message': "Using sys.exit(main()) instead of main()

As we known, Exceptions are raised by the sys.exit()function. When they
are not handled, no stack traceback is printed in the Python interpreter.

In this patch we have known main() got return values(eg:0, 1), but it
can't specifies exit status when terminate the main thread by unusing
sys.exit(). So when using sys.exit(main()) instead of main() may be
more readable and reasonable.

TrivialFix.

Change-Id: I9fd3cf28ea1c83022f7b4f03f606b881efa9f4db
"}]
commit_message:
Using sys.exit(main()) instead of main()

As we known, Exceptions are raised by the sys.exit()function. When they
are not handled, no stack traceback is printed in the Python interpreter.

In this patch we have known main() got return values(eg:0, 1), but it
can't specifies exit status when terminate the main thread by unusing
sys.exit(). So when using sys.exit(main()) instead of main() may be
more readable and reasonable.

TrivialFix.

Change-Id: I9fd3cf28ea1c83022f7b4f03f606b881efa9f4db

commit_message:
Remove non-locking accounts from the config guide

Before Tempest had three different methods of providing authentication,
dynamic credentials, locking test accounts and non-locking test
accounts, currently only the first two are supported. This commit
updates a section on the configuration guide where it still mentions
three methods.

Change-Id: I532aff27a803b9fd34e994153f4183de48d91d00
Closes-Bug: 1600319

commit_message:
Always use context manager for DB transactions

An exception could occur at any time, so we want to make sure we roll
back any uncompleted transaction when that happens.

Change-Id: Id0d5b65f44981bde24840b8a0d5fdc0b88f24d8a
Related-bug: #1546431

commit_message:
Preventing iptables rule to be thrashed

When update meter label or rule, iptables_manager will update iptables
rule in router's namespace. In order to, it will clean traffic counter
number collected in interval time, the other iptables always trashing
that will clean old iptalbes rule and generate new same significance
iptables rule.

Change-Id: Ide2b26c98587258175234acded38ce481b7e7f76
Closes-Bug: #1618879

commit_message:
Delete alternate DB migration branches

Delete all DB alternative migrations that were
incorporated into the main migration branch
and not present anymore. The fact that the
database contains unknown version identifiers
causes alembic migration to fail even though
there is no other migration that depends on it.

Change-Id: I4201e9b310eb04f26927e8f66ee986c27fa160ae

commit_message:
Allow for invalid packet sequence in keepalive

In the SQLAlchemy keep_alive class, MariaDB is failing
as pymysql reports an invalid packet sequence.
MariaDB seems to timeout the client in a different
way than MySQL and PXC, which manifests itself as the
aforementioned invalid sequence.  It is now handled
as a special-case exception.

With this fix, the MariaDB scenario tests now pass.

The scenario tests were also tweaked a bit, which aided
in the testing of the fix.  'group=instance' was created,
plus instance_error properly interleaved with
instance_create.  _has_status now calls get_instance with
the admin client so that any faults are accompanied by
a relevant stack trace.  Cases where the result code
was being checked out-of-sequence were removed, and explicit
calls to check the http code for the right client were added.

The replication error messages for promote and eject were
enhanced as well to attempt to debug spurious failures.
One of those failures was 'Replication is not on after 60 seconds.'
This was fixed by setting 'MASTER_CONNECT_RETRY' in the mariadb
gtid replication strategy as was done in:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/188933

Finally, backup_incremental was added to MariaDB supported
groups and cleaned up elsewhere.

Closes-Bug: #1621702
Change-Id: Id6bde5a34e1d79eece3084f761dcd153c38ccbad

commit_message:
Ensure tempest runs independently in testing

In tempest role tests we install tempest on a container that already has
other services installed on it.

To ensure the tempest role is indepedent we should test it by deploying
it in it's own container.

We need to fix the dependencies for the tempest role by installing git
on the tempest host.

Change-Id: I0230f1a93d16243fc50df79b2d0780e744706c7b

commit_message:
Add edge case tests for disabling a trustee

This commit introduces two tests that ensures if a trustee of a
trust-scoped token is disabled, keystone will emit a Forbidden
exception. Regardless of the token provider, keystone should have
a consistent behavior. In order to test this, the test had to be
implemented differently for each token provider, specifically for
persistent and non-persistent tokens.

Co-Authored-By: Lance Bragstad <lbragstad@gmail.com>
Change-Id: Iaf04a26c9f60eb68bbd56b941ff76c893c144cb8

the call. This broke the neutron-lbaas gate. This commit updates the

commit_message:
Fix links on configure_federation documentation

When the API reference was moved and the old pages cleaned up, a lot of
dead links were created. This patch fixes them for the documentation on
"Configuring Keystone for Federation".

Moreover, a lot of the link text was nondescriptive, which makes the
documentation inaccessible for screen readers (see the W3C
guideline[1]). This patch cleans that up as well if the link URL
needed to be updated anyway.

[1] https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20-TECHS/H30.html

Change-Id: I58803276d9b06bad0252da2494c81a46c951916f

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-09-13 19:51:26.000000000', 'files': ['functions.sh'], 'message': 'Handle multiline env vars in reproduce.sh

Our old reproduce.sh env var processing was line based which meant we
mangled multiline env var values. Switch to using null delimiters when
processing the env vars so that we can preserve any multiline env vars.

Change-Id: Ia0756baf0dfea790d489f7cbff68c0ec5887b3d1

commit_message:
Handle multiline env vars in reproduce.sh

Our old reproduce.sh env var processing was line based which meant we
mangled multiline env var values. Switch to using null delimiters when
processing the env vars so that we can preserve any multiline env vars.

Change-Id: Ia0756baf0dfea790d489f7cbff68c0ec5887b3d1

commit_message:
Implement full online backups for DB2

Currently Trove supports full offline backups for DB2. In this
implementation, we have added support for full online backups for DB2
using archival logging.

Change-Id: I30b5b0b85120fd105cc3db57983b062fad5fab5a
Implements: blueprint db2-online-backup

subject: Provide information related to haproxy and mysql
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-09-13 20:30:38.000000000', 'files': ['README.md'], 'message': 'Provide information related to haproxy and mysql

When using HA Proxy to front MySQL, the issue becomes that the way
the client/server handle the connection it will cause HA Proxy to
leave ports in TIME_WAIT and then exhaust all available TCP ports.
The information provided will give insight on the issue and also ways
to tune HA Proxy to handle the high connections to MySQL.

Change-Id: I427fa5ff8249387362911dd2637b4c5002e7177d
'}]
commit_message:
Provide information related to haproxy and mysql

When using HA Proxy to front MySQL, the issue becomes that the way
the client/server handle the connection it will cause HA Proxy to
leave ports in TIME_WAIT and then exhaust all available TCP ports.
The information provided will give insight on the issue and also ways
to tune HA Proxy to handle the high connections to MySQL.

Change-Id: I427fa5ff8249387362911dd2637b4c5002e7177d

subject: Fixes KeyError while updating bgp peer
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-08 15:23:08.000000000', 'files': ['neutron_dynamic_routing/db/bgp_db.py', 'neutron_dynamic_routing/tests/unit/db/test_bgp_db.py'], 'message': "Fixes KeyError while updating bgp peer

This will fix the issue of KeyError being thrown when
'password' is not supplied while updating bgp peer.
The dict get() method is used to return None when
'password' key is not available.

Two unit tests are also added which will test the cases
1) Exception thrown if the auth type is 'none', and a
password is supplied when updating
2) When the password is not supplied

Change-Id: Ief9e88ca12b04eb08b0cc4e60f9d883f1e282ae9
Closes-Bug: #1616066
"}]
commit_message:
Fixes KeyError while updating bgp peer

This will fix the issue of KeyError being thrown when
'password' is not supplied while updating bgp peer.
The dict get() method is used to return None when
'password' key is not available.

Two unit tests are also added which will test the cases
1) Exception thrown if the auth type is 'none', and a
password is supplied when updating
2) When the password is not supplied

Change-Id: Ief9e88ca12b04eb08b0cc4e60f9d883f1e282ae9
Closes-Bug: #1616066

commit_message:
Remove cyclic import between rpcapi and objects.base

There was a cyclic import between conductor.rpcapi and objects.base,
this was initally fixed by doing an import at runtime. This patch fixes
the import cycle for good.

Change-Id: I8ee8c47652de75430312f77ddee08adc7a237d2b
Closes-Bug: #1623074

commit_message:
NetApp cDOT: Fix reporting of replication capabilities

Host level replication capability was added to the NetApp
cDOT Block and File drivers through
I87b92e76d0d5022e9be610b9e237b89417309c05.
However, the replication capability was not being reported
at the pool level.

Add the field at pool level allowing for compatibility with
volume types that may include the `replication_enabled`
extra-spec.

Change-Id: Ic735a527c609166884668c84c589da521769500b
Closes-Bug: #1615451

commit_message:
mariadb service fix

kolla genconfig currently requires mariadb to listen on
kolla_internal_vip_address. Until we fix it in genconfig
to use dns, this works around the issue.

commit_message:
Module re-apply does not reflect updated values

If you apply a module, remove it, update the module with a new name,
and apply it again, module-query will still show the old name.

This also applies to datastore, datastore_version and type.

All four attributes are now updated correctly and scenario
tests added.

When writing the scenario tests it became evident that resetting
a module from a datastore to all_datastores was broken too,
so this was fixed (along with all_datastore_versions).  This
fix required a change to the Trove client as well.

Change-Id: Ic2e9226bcd31c4a79d84ecb7941a47875eabd73d
Depends-On: I0f226f09db08f635c542b27d8d2f898050d327fa
Closes-Bug: #1611525
Closes-Bug: #1612430

commit_message:
More track-upstream for packaging_deb

As some new deb-* project, after the initialization phase to take the Git
from Alioth, we need to set the correct upstream: field and the
track-upstream option.

Also correctly fixes https://git.openstack.org/openstack/ceilometermiddleware
as upstream for deb-python-ceilometermiddleware.

Change-Id: I2450d4040116a9fedd7d6d5cbbc773f0c3502ef7

commit_message:
Do not move task status to running after ack

Astute will send 'running' status for task
when start to process it, so we do not need
task in orchestrator mechanism.

Change-Id: I5e2deccdbd27daff3e3b131ef9c8c7ffbbb40dd4

commit_message:
Fixed problems prevented for calling core serializers from extensions.

Added option skip_extensions for core-serializers, to prevent
loop when core-serializer is called from extension.
Also method process_'deployment_for_node' does not have access
to cluster_info and it is not possible to call 'serialize_node'
from extension because cluster_info was mandatory argument.
Because 'cluster_info' was needed only for provision serialzer,
which is called from LCM serializer, this argument was removed
from serialze_node method.

Change-Id: Ifbf9e4a0b9487605e6268fde0499aecc1e20cb36
Closes-Bug: 1621851

commit_message:
Allow gnocchi to make use of keystone authentication

The upstream default implementation of gnocchi is not
to use keystone authentication, but a preferred deployment
configuration in enterprise environments is to ensure that
keystone authentication is configured.

commit_message:
Pass not IPDevice but port_name into OVSBridge's add_port()

The use_veth_interconnection config doesn't work fine because
IPDevice is passed into OVSBridge's add_port() although the method
expects port_name. This patch fixes the wrong argument.

Change-Id: I6ea3e37d857f34228c41118709b91f4407555a33
Closes-Bug: #1622850

commit_message:
Add command to delete BUILD instances and clusters

Sometimes an instance/cluster can be stuck in BUILD state forever.
Attempting to delete the instance in this state is currently not
allowed. Add force-delete and reset-status command. Reset-status
will reset the status of an instance to ERROR and cluster to NONE.

The reset-status command can only be used if the instance/cluster
is in BUILD or ERROR state. Resetting the status of an instance in
ERROR state can be useful as an instance might go ACTIVE after the
specified timeout. Once the status has been reset it is possible
for an instance to go ACTIVE if it receives a hearbeat from the
guestagent.

Force-delete will combine functionality of reset-status and delete.

Change-Id: I83f6cdcdd884e51d002295b0d1f07341990e512c
Depends-On: I957b4be5030e493e0eb8c6b6855d41b942b2823c
Partial-Bug: #1579141

commit_message:
More conservative inventory updates

This makes the compute node check for the current inventory,
compare it to the one it would send to the placement service, and
only make the PUT call if updates are needed. This results in lower
write traffic to the DB, fewer generation conflicts, etc.

It also aggressively tries to refresh its view of the remote generation,
which is now changing on every allocation as well, to avoid needing to
retry inventory updates later.

Change-Id: Id846f184c569341ae96e1696cb95e7f901e27f66

subject: Put the regex first
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-10 01:37:41.000000000', 'files': ['devstack-vm-gate.sh'], 'message': "Put the regex first

This commit swaps the argument order of tempest tox jobs that use a
regex to specify a subset of tests to run. This is necessary for some
future changes to the tempest tox definitions that will switch it from
using a testr wrapping bash script to the tempest run command instead.
With tempest run you specify a regex with a '--regex' parameter and to
keep backwards compatibility this is added to the tempest tox
definitions. However this breaks on devstack-gate because we pass the
concurrency in before the regex. This ends up having a call equivalent
to:

  tempest run --regex --concurrency=2 $REGEX

which obviously is incorrect. Simply switching the arg order should work
in both cases. It's also worth pointing out that this is a temporary
step as we will migrate devstack-gate to call tempest init and tempest
run directly.

Change-Id: I8786b9709584378aaf48393115dda94397e22544
Need-by: I3684fce66a799579fa68af119652cafef25a9f03
"}]
commit_message:
Put the regex first

This commit swaps the argument order of tempest tox jobs that use a
regex to specify a subset of tests to run. This is necessary for some
future changes to the tempest tox definitions that will switch it from
using a testr wrapping bash script to the tempest run command instead.
With tempest run you specify a regex with a '--regex' parameter and to
keep backwards compatibility this is added to the tempest tox
definitions. However this breaks on devstack-gate because we pass the
concurrency in before the regex. This ends up having a call equivalent
to:

  tempest run --regex --concurrency=2 $REGEX

which obviously is incorrect. Simply switching the arg order should work
in both cases. It's also worth pointing out that this is a temporary
step as we will migrate devstack-gate to call tempest init and tempest
run directly.

Change-Id: I8786b9709584378aaf48393115dda94397e22544

commit_message:
Distributed cache namespace to invalidate regions

dogpile.cache's region invalidation is not designed to work across
processes. This patch enables distributed invalidation of keys in a
region.

Instead of using a static cache key, we use the original cache key
and append a dynamic value to it. This value is looked up in
memcached using the region name as a key. So anytime the value of
the region key changes the cache keys in that region are
effectively invalidated.

Closes-Bug: #1590779
(cherry picked from commit 42eda48c78f1153081b4c193dc13c88561409fd3)

 Conflicts:
	keystone/assignment/core.py
	keystone/catalog/core.py
	keystone/common/cache/core.py
	keystone/identity/core.py
	keystone/revoke/core.py
	keystone/server/backends.py
	keystone/tests/unit/test_v3_assignment.py
	keystone/token/provider.py

Change-Id: I6ac3743880a7646482e1117d8307b493dbe50ea0

commit_message:
Mark quota operations as retriable

This decorates the quota system operations with
the retry decorators. This will help significantly
with the bug this marks as closed since operations
in the quota engine after commit should no longer
trigger retries of the full API operation.

The logic to find the args in the decorator had
to be adjusted to deal with functions already decorated.
This just uses the getargspec function from pecan that
deals with decorated functions.

Partial-Bug: #1612798
Closes-Bug: #1596075
Change-Id: Ib786117dcea08af75551770ea4c30d460382b829

commit_message:
Update BuildRequest if instance currently being scheduled

There are some cases where the instance is still waiting to be scheduled and
consequently there is still a BuildRequest object where we would also like to
update the instance attributes, like the display name.

In that case, we need to update the nested instance field from the BuildRequest
instead of trying to update the instance object itself, which could be located
in a child cell.

Change-Id: I97cd6dbae10ca1a29f646b0b25bc08edd699edca
Closes-Bug: #1620248

commit_message:
Keep consistent order for regenerated configs

There's a bug in glance_store ( bug 1619487 ) that results in a
reordering of the store related configurations everytime the tool to
autogenerate configs is used.

This commit generates the Newton config in the deterministic way by
using the suggested solution described on the bug.

For more information and background discussions see change
Iea2c538b37182191445cc5c1f8b2d9dceed06343

Related-Change: I3146b8597a5d89da49b84d6653edacc3067c2c71

Change-Id: Idbea98865ccfc14563ab4357764383e1e7021542

commit_message:
Add entry points for each gateway classes

This patch adds entry points for each gateway classes to enable
users to use these entry point name in the gateway congifration,
while we also can use the full class path for the gatewaay class.

For example, we can configure
 gateway_class = docker
or
 gateway_class = storlet_gateway.gateways.docker.StorletGatewayDocker
to load docker gateway.

Change-Id: Iffbd55bd46bb8259a91ecb261188e78088a34811

commit_message:
Add tag for tempest plugins

This commit adds a new deliverable type tag to describe tempest
plugins. For right now this is just for standalone plugin repos.
However the vast majority of tempest plugins are packaged in the
project repos. This is actually an anti-pattern and makes consuming
it more difficult. [1] But, cleaning that up is a separate matter. In
the interim it might be worth adding the tag to those repos with
included plugins as well. But that is a separate discussion to have
and will happen in, a follow on change.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/tempest/plugin.html#standalone-plugin-vs-in-repo-plugin

Change-Id: Ia713945e88f9f207f9a260eb83b9e595629c4bc3

commit_message:
Add tag for devstack plugins

This commit adds a new deliverable type tag to describe devstack
plugins. For right now this is just for standalone plugin repos.
However the vast majority of devstack plugins are packaged in the
project repos. It might be worth adding the tag to those repos as
well. But that is a separate discussion to have and will happen in,
a follow one change.

Change-Id: Ia4484793a11810a0835d12f1ea7e1e1bb3d66e18

commit_message:
Revert "Add caching to role assignments"

The method of caching used does not invalidate cache across processes.
This leads to false-positive cache hits.

This reverts commit cd906266e67c8a8a8ae9676d2fa6dd1bd2f59bd8.
Closes-Bug: 1590779

Change-Id: Ia0963106a0ca557d9ae7a7981c49332b62b0c67f

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-23 16:20:21.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/common/kvs/backends/memcached.py'], 'message': 'Tweak memcache lock sleep time and attempts number

Experiments shows that operations inside the lock usually take much less
than 1 second, which is the worst case of random.random(). The solution
is to increase the number of attempts to acquire the lock more oftenly.

Set sleep time to a number in interval [0, 0.01] and increase the number of
attempts to acquire the lock to 1500.

Change-Id: If07401856c667dafdde3984ee0097ebaca401db4
'}]
commit_message:
Tweak memcache lock sleep time and attempts number

Experiments shows that operations inside the lock usually take much less
than 1 second, which is the worst case of random.random(). The solution
is to increase the number of attempts to acquire the lock more oftenly.

Set sleep time to a number in interval [0, 0.01] and increase the number of
attempts to acquire the lock to 1500.

Change-Id: If07401856c667dafdde3984ee0097ebaca401db4

subject: Fix inheritance of memcache client used in pool
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-12-04 18:22:58.000000000', 'files': ['keystonemiddleware/auth_token/_memcache_pool.py'], 'message': 'Fix inheritance of memcache client used in pool

memcache.Client became inherited from threading._local so instances are only
accessible from current thread or eventlet. Present workaround broke
inheritance chain so super() call is unusable.

This patch makes artificial client class mimic inheritance from
threading._local while using generic object methods allowing
reusability.

Change-Id: I8dd165e4bac3e368c3526a518f18eccf528b3240
Partial-Bug: 1463009
'}]
commit_message:
Fix inheritance of memcache client used in pool

memcache.Client became inherited from threading._local so instances are only
accessible from current thread or eventlet. Present workaround broke
inheritance chain so super() call is unusable.

This patch makes artificial client class mimic inheritance from
threading._local while using generic object methods allowing
reusability.

Change-Id: I8dd165e4bac3e368c3526a518f18eccf528b3240
Partial-Bug: 1463009

commit_message:
Replace key manager with Castellan

Because key manager code is duplicated across several projects, a key
manager interface was moved into its own library. This goes back to
replace the old code with the new library.

Implements: blueprint use-castellan-key-manager
Change-Id: Ief8885bb4ca8d62b03cf1a52c25dd0e62c835bfe

commit_message:
Handling NeutronClientException and translating it to HTTP 503

When neutron service is down, we get a HTTP 500. Handling the Neutron client
exception in the security_group_api code and translating it to a NovaException
and handling that and raising an HTTP 503 where security_group_api is called.

closes-bug:1437863
Change-Id: Icdaf4cd9b57d5411f4984274da99c6d75cf1022e

commit_message:
Reorder the compute config options page

I reordered the existing content into a structure like:
* intro
* quickstart
* full details

People not familiar with the config options of Nova are now
able to quickly find all possible options to get a rough understanding
what's possible. Operators will be mostly interested in new, changed
and deprecated options, which is also more prominent at the top now.

Change-Id: I11326311de9fb82d825bfb8b384105131fa5c0e1

commit_message:
Tests verify cluster data via every node

Cluster tests currently verify data only via the first node.
This may easily miss bugs when data is not properly replicated
within the cluster due to some configuration issue.

Change-Id: I9e280aeaa1e83eb1902b83f64a5e1d5bf2ba7a4f

commit_message:
Generate HTML API docs from Swagger YAML

Define the Magnum API in Swagger YAML format, and add tools to generate
HTML documentation from this artifact.

The source Swagger definition
(api-ref/source/container-infra-v1-swagger.yaml) was inspired by the
prototype that Jamie Hannaford <jamie.hannaford@rackspace.com> produced.
See https://github.com/jamiehannaford/swagger-magnum.

This patch also contains several changes which were adapted from a
proposed patch to the `api-site` project. For details on that patch, see
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/286659/.

The `tools/build-api-ref-swagger.sh` was copied from the `api-site`
project and modified with some changes from
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/286659/. I've made some of my own
modifications, but it's important to acknowledge that a good portion of
this work must be credited to: Michael Krotscheck <krotscheck@gmail.com>

Finally, it's worth noting that https://review.openstack.org/#/c/303235
is an ongoing attempt to generate API docs automatically by
instrumenting the Magnum source code. Once that work is complete, it can
be easily knitted into this workflow to generate API docs straight from
the source code.

Change-Id: I33c9db86fd96efba789e6cf86214f2b4bc38d024
Closes-Bug: 1460161

commit_message:
Fixes ZFSSANFS driver

The change to use versionedobjects in remotefs.py left the
ZFSSANFS driver broken. This is to fix will change the
create_volume and clone_image to use objects instead of dictionary.

It also adds 'cinder_managed' tag that was missing when creating
volumes from snapshots.

Change-Id: I1fe0516a98c37ad126a206254379c85598235635
Closes-Bug: #1602421

commit_message:
devstack: the last fix of is_kernel_supported_for_ovs25 condition

Previously we didn't consider kernels higher than 4. This patch returns
True right away if the verions is lesser than 4. If it is 4, then it must
be lesser or equal to 3 to return True. All other versions are not
supported.

Change-Id: I3e9fa088d7cb9cfecbe7670c84a051e15be2a3a9

commit_message:
Fix volume retype from SolidFire

During retype from SolidFire to something else SolidFire driver
tries to delete volume with temporaty ID and fails. Once retype
finished succesfully, we've got original volume stored at SolidFire
storage.

Change-Id: I4fb23b890415fb32dd8d98c690bf8c40f3885446
Closes-Bug: #1610172
(cherry picked from commit a8e3220bd8e03697dd7ae1f34bf4e678558a46ed)

commit_message:
Fix the password print in cinder-volume.log issue

In cinder.conf replication_device may contains replication
remote device password,and in cinder.volume.driver secret
is not set 'true' for replication_device, So when start cinder
volume service,replication remote device sensitive information
will print in cinder volume log, it will cause some security
problems.

This commit fixes that by setting secret=true for replication_device
in cinder.volume.driver.

Change-Id: I710b557768ca3df0303d70b43b3c74247eed6b24
Closes-Bug: #1617534
(cherry picked from commit 033284a419e4c6d550e253de2a88a50aaac4922e)

commit_message:
Fix volume retype from SolidFire

During retype from SolidFire to something else SolidFire driver
tries to delete volume with temporaty ID and fails. Once retype
finished succesfully, we've got original volume stored at SolidFire
storage.

Change-Id: I4fb23b890415fb32dd8d98c690bf8c40f3885446
Closes-Bug: #1610172
(cherry picked from commit a8e3220bd8e03697dd7ae1f34bf4e678558a46ed)

Adds templates for Glance images + members. Also tweaks the HTTP parser
so that it doesn't break with a PATCH body consisting of a list instead
of the more-common dict. This solution is sub-optimal because the body
is treated as a string variable (i.e. you'll get a fuzzed request like

Change-Id: I0e23c8281a63018ecadb84959f3a70be1f80fa74
"}]
commit_message:
Glance Images Templates

Adds templates for Glance images + members. Also tweaks the HTTP parser
so that it doesn't break with a PATCH body consisting of a list instead
of the more-common dict. This solution is sub-optimal because the body
is treated as a string variable (i.e. you'll get a fuzzed request like
[0x0000] instead of fuzzing the contained object attributes)

Change-Id: I0e23c8281a63018ecadb84959f3a70be1f80fa74

commit_message:
Cast sets to lists in acl functional tests

``acl_users`` can be either a set or a list. As long as
Python sets are not JSON serializable, cast them to lists
in functional tests.

This way we avoid gate failures like [1].

[1]
http://logs.openstack.org/46/319446/7/check/gate-python-barbicanclient-devstack-dsvm/cb80e0c/console.html#_2016-08-04_15_38_51_649177

Change-Id: I6b8601f7168120cf0e15716cc22b8834ddb127e8

commit_message:
Using count() instead of all() for getting incompleted tasks

* Workflow completion check logic used heavy select query which
  actually returned objects whereas all we need is to count them.
  This patch adds get_incompleted_task_executions_count() methods
  on DB API to address this.

Change-Id: I796ba175210f41ded7877f310efeb30bd5045531

subject: Stop using tox venv in run_tests.sh
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2016-05-05 21:27:07.000000000', 'files': ['run_tests.sh'], 'message': "Stop using tox venv in run_tests.sh

This commit moves tempest from using a tox venv with site-packages
enabled to use an independently created venv which is really isolated.
The advantage here is that run_tests.sh owns the venv and doesn't rely
on calling to private dirs it assumes tox is creating. Note, this has
the further advantage on stable branches of having complete isolation.
Running tempest in a venv with site-packages enabled with stable
branches is a bad idea because tempest follows global requirements for
master so eventually you'll have a version conflict between master and

Change-Id: Id1c69bd67d843145a72987a8d984ee3aaf4a8143
"}]
commit_message:
Stop using tox venv in run_tests.sh

This commit moves tempest from using a tox venv with site-packages
enabled to use an independently created venv which is really isolated.
The advantage here is that run_tests.sh owns the venv and doesn't rely
on calling to private dirs it assumes tox is creating. Note, this has
the further advantage on stable branches of having complete isolation.
Running tempest in a venv with site-packages enabled with stable
branches is a bad idea because tempest follows global requirements for
master so eventually you'll have a version conflict between master and
stable.

Change-Id: Id1c69bd67d843145a72987a8d984ee3aaf4a8143

User name use kubernetes instead of minion

It is unfriendly to ssh master nodes by minion user: ssh minion@master_ip
we can create user which named 'kubernetes' on nodes, then login nodes:
ssh kubernetes@master_ip or ssh kubernetes@minion_ip

commit_message:
Report underlying integer for unknown capabilities

Ieb1ea2ab45d76fc838c11489c2b029d7a5295e0e added a fix to report unknown
capabilities as "CAP_UNDEFINED".  This change improves on that slightly
to use `str(c)` for undefined capabilities rather than losing
information.  This also better parallels the oslo.config "input"
behaviour in `priv_context.CapNameOrInt`

Change-Id: Ic59576a4eba7bb8d40aee9e3d383417386aa08aa

I believe this is the correct behavior, as it would match how
containers handles these operations. This change facilitates
the LBaaS Barbican TLS workflow (which should be the same as

The RBAC settings for consumer POST should be set to
use the same ACL rules as container GET (plus admin).

The RBAC settings for consumer DELETE should be:
 * Any user with Delete permissions on the Container
 * Any user that both: has ACL Read access to the Container; is a member
   of the project that created the Consumer being deleted

commit_message:
Remove consumer check for project_id to match containers

I believe this is the correct behavior, as it would match how
containers handles these operations. This change facilitates
the LBaaS Barbican TLS workflow (which should be the same as
what other services will use in the future too).

The RBAC settings for consumer POST should be set to
use the same ACL rules as container GET (plus admin).

The RBAC settings for consumer DELETE should be:
 * Any user with Delete permissions on the Container
 * Any user that both: has ACL Read access to the Container; is a member
   of the project that created the Consumer being deleted

Change-Id: Ie84784573893934c2887814a200e7386314b4f18
Closes-Bug: #1519170

commit_message:
Use ResourceGroup synthetic attributes

Fn::Select is not available in the 2015-10-15 Heat template version or
later. This patch replaces the use of Fn::Select with the retrieval of
a particular node's attribute through ResourceGroup's synthetic
attributes since it is supported in all Heat template versions.

Change-Id: I76fe8dc7929298a043d918f73e1b47733c06ae52

commit_message:
Add Container Volume Model into Swarm Heat Templates

Previously,the swarm bay type did not support the Magnum Container
Volume Model. This patch adds support for volume through the following:

1. Add username, tenant_name, preempt, region_name, domain_name to
swarm bay type.
2. Update swarm unit tests to support container volume.
3. Update swarm heat templates for container volume model

Change-Id: Ie5e78e6b9d06fd2c92915b8635b8062c008e9696
Partially-Implements: blueprint magnum-integrate-with-cinder

commit_message:
Add external CA certs to baymodel

Magnum requires that a bay connects to Magnum's public API, this public
API may require an HTTPS connection. To verify this TLS connection a
custom cert for this endpoint is needed.

This patch allows passing in of an optional CA certificate to baymodel
which can be used to verify connections to publicURLs. This cert will be
passed into the bay at creation and is added to the bundle. This CA cert
can be used for authenticating any custom external TLS certificates in a
standard corporate environment.

This patch only adds support for the fedora kubernetes bay, further patches
will enable other distros and other COEs.

An associated patch will be included for magnumclient to upload a cert.

Change-Id: I4eebb07755d16da6f01aa2b667b8ff3e56824f93
Partial-Bug: 1580704

commit_message:
Make kube_version become a member of the lable attr

Kubernetes Container Volume Model needs kubernetes
version >= 1.1.1, but now kubernetes image is 1.0.6.
It is neccessary to modify the kubernetes version by users.
For Kubernetes Container Volume Model can use this new image,
which has Kubernetes 1.1.8. It is based on the stock image from Atomic:
https://fedorapeople.org/groups/magnum/fedora-23-atomic-7.qcow2
So when creating the baymodel with labels kube_version=v1.1.8, the volume
feature can be used.

The patch can change the kubernetes image version when user need different
image version.

Depends-On: I8f568087f8e8254cb14a81edb526e596da33abcc

commit_message:
Add flavor/service provider support to routers

This is the initial support for flavors and multiple service
providers with the built-in L3 service plugin.

This patch handles a few key components:

* Adds an optional flavor_id to the router data model
* Adds a new driver controller that performs the following tasks:
  * Loads up the configured drivers and 4 default drivers representing
    the current matrix of ha/dvr options (single node, ha, dvr, and ha+dvr)
  * Associates every router with a driver based on ha/dvr attributes
    or the flavor_id if specified

Note that the current drivers are very limited because they don't do anything.
All of the complex logic for the in-tree drivers is still tied up in the giant
mixin the service plugin inherits. Breaking that apart will be in follow-up
patches.

Partially-Implements: blueprint multi-l3-backends
Change-Id: Idce75bf0fc1375dcbbff9b9803fd2fe97d158cff

commit_message:
python3: Repalce the six.iteritems with items()

In py3: we avoid using six.iteritems/keys achieve iterators.
we can use dict.items/keys instead, as it will return iterators
in py3 as well, alao dict.items/keys vill more readable.

Here two links for more details,
[1] introduce the progress of python 3 effort porting for openstack
    https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3
[2] a discussion suggesting to avoid six , thanks Robert Collins
    http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/066391.html

Change-Id: I03a6d374d2d5e06673bec30f1d03fa5bfafd4eb1

commit_message:
Make the file name for user_secrets a variable

Some downstream vendors may not have their secrets files in the
location openstack-ansible expects.  Here we allow them to set a
variable for the filename where they are storing secrets within.

Fixes-Bug: 1621938
Depends-On: I6578502ede4132f6764c3a77208505a28d1ba247
Change-Id: I1ccb908f8048cea54e2c2a1c2af20e6c976072b9

commit_message:
Add edge case test for disabling a trustee

This commit introduces two tests that ensures if a trustee of a
trust-scoped token is disabled, keystone will emit a Forbidden
exception. Regardless of the token provider, keystone should emit
a consistent behavior. In order to test this, the test had to be
implemented differently for each token provider, specifically for
persistent and non-persistent tokens.

Change-Id: Ie0ef1cd442e41df06a3367de4e4175deef0965f8
